<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE: that is the chapter's point made by the build. The value types copy in and
    copy out (Item 50) and the immutable records carry no exposed mutable state, so the
    representation-exposure detectors (EI_EXPOSE_REP / EI_EXPOSE_REP2) stay quiet without any
    suppression. The service holds only an injected interface port, which SpotBugs does not treat as
    a leak. The filter is kept (empty) so a future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a home with a
    reason, rather than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
